楔.definition: wedge; to hammer in (variant of 揳[xie1])

楔嘴鷯鶥.definition: (bird species of China) Cachar wedge-billed babbler (Sphenocichla roberti)

楔子.definition: wedge; peg; stopper; prologue (in some modern novels); prologue or interlude in Yuan dynasty drama

楔尾伯勞.definition: (bird species of China) Chinese grey shrike (Lanius sphenocercus)

楔尾綠鳩.definition: (bird species of China) wedge-tailed green pigeon (Treron sphenurus)

楔尾鷗.definition: (bird species of China) Ross's gull (Rhodostethia rosea)
